Usage: create_ccopt_generated_clock_tree [-help] [-name <clockname>]
                                         [-parents <parents>] -source <pin>
                                         [-stop_at_sdc_clock_roots] [ -search_method <method> | -generated_by <pins> ]

-help                        # Prints out the command usage
-generated_by <pins>         # sink pins in the parent clock trees from which
                             # this clock tree is generated
                             # ((instTerm|term)+, optional)
-name <clockname>            # user-defined identifier for this generated clock
                             # tree (string, optional)
-parents <parents>           # parent clock trees for the generated clock tree
                             # (string, optional)
-search_method {same_instance multi_stage}
                             # search methodology to be used when tracing the
                             # path to the generator inputs (enum, optional)
-source <pin>                # source pin of the generated clock tree
                             # ((instTerm|term), required)
-stop_at_sdc_clock_roots     # stop searching for parts of the clock tree
                             # through SDC clock roots (bool, optional)